"21514D5500A17A1 Ver:A1", a date code of '''1322''', and lead-free logo, :is silkscreened on the wireless module in the FCC photos. Two marked antennae are shown - :"PCA-2825-A1" is on one, "PCA-2010-" + "A14" is on another.
This [https://fccid.io/KA2IR862LA1/RF-Exposure-Info/RF-Exposure-Info-MPE-pdf-2410188 FCC submission] shows the DIR-862L (AC1600, WL1 MIMO 2x2:2) has the same ID as the DIR-866L (AC1750, WL1 MIMO 3x3:3): RF EXPOSURE REPORT REPORT NO.: SA131227C19E MODEL NO.: DIR-862L, DIR-866L FCC ID: KA2IR862LA1 APPLICANT: D-Link Corporation PRODUCT: Wireless AC1600 Dual Band Gigabit Cloud Router, AC1750 Wi-Fi Router
The DIR-862L main board ''appears'' to be the same used by the [[D-Link DIR-863 rev A1|DIR-863]], and also uses the [[Qualcomm_Atheros#SoC|QCA9558 WiSoC]]. There is an unpopulated spot on the board for a NAND Flash IC, and the 863L uses two 16MB flash chips. Another source indicates the DIR-866L FCC ID matches that of the DIR863L.
